                <h1>Quick Guide: Create a White Background in Photoshop</h1>
                <p>To create a white background in Photoshop, start by opening your image. Use the Magic Wand Tool to select the area you want to change to white. Adjust the tolerance for better selection. Press Delete to clear the selected area. Then, create a new layer filled with white, positioning it behind your image layer. Save your work!</p>
